tion is shorter and\nfatter. The arm-length ratio seems to be correlated with the misalignment angle\nbetween the two sides of the radio source and strongly anti-correlated with the\naxial ratio, consistent with environmental effects and/or a change in the\noutflow direction. In this sample, asymmetries in the local environments and/or\nmotion of the outflow axis are likely to be more important than relativistic\nbeaming effects.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Feb 2007 01:00:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 30 May 2007 15:40:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-09-15"}
